Device Name: Ubuntu_Server-1
Operating System: Ubuntu Linux
Virtualization Platform: VirtualBox
Memory: 4096 MB
Network Adapter: Intel PRO/1000 MT Desktop (82540EM)

Network Configuration:
- Connected to Switch1
- One Ethernet adapter
- Uses IPv4 addressing
- Provides network services to the Windows 10 client

Configured Services:
- DHCP
- DNS
- HTTP
- TCP and UDP communication

DHCP Function:
The Ubuntu server provides automatic IP configuration to the client.
The DHCP process includes Discover, Offer, Request, and Acknowledgment
messages.

DNS Function:
The server provides hostname-to-IP-address resolution. DNS operation
was tested from the Windows 10 client with nslookup.

HTTP Function:
A web service was hosted on the Ubuntu server and tested from the
Windows 10 client using a web browser and the curl command.

Verification Commands:
ip addr
ip route
systemctl status isc-dhcp-server
systemctl status bind9
systemctl status nginx
ss -tulpn
